original: Cervin, Gunnar, kyrkoherde, Gravarne, f. 13/3/93 i Okome, Hall. I, av prosten Reinhold C. o. Maria Cullberg. G. 25 m. Greta Olsson. Barn: Ingvar f. 27, Torsten 34. — Stud:ex. i Halmstad 12, teol. fil. ex. 13, teol. kand. 16, prästv. f. Gbgs stift 17. Pastors-adj. i Västra Frölunda 17, kyrkoh. i Kungshamn sed. 23.
translated: Cervin, Gunnar, clergyman, Gravarne, b. March 13, 1893 in Okome, Halland. Son of the dean Reinhold C. and Maria Cullberg. Married on August 25, 19xx to Greta Olsson. Children: Ingvar, b. 1927 and Torsten, b. 1934. He graduated from high school in Halmstad in 1912, earned a Bachelor of Theology degree in 1913, a Master of Theology degree in 1916, and was ordained as a priest for the Gothenburg Diocese in 1917. He served as a pastor's assistant in Västra Frölunda in 1917 before becoming the vicar of Kungshamn in 1923.
